From: Florent Revest <revestflo@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 9 Jun 2026 22:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] amplifiers: cl_dsp: return -ENOENT when a coeff control is
 not found

cl_dsp_get_reg() only assigns *reg inside the lookup loop, when a
matching coefficient descriptor is found. If no descriptor matches
(e.g. the cs40l26-codec "A2H Level" kcontrol getter looking up
"VOLUMELEVEL" in the A2H algo before any cs40l26-a2h.bin coefficient
file has been loaded), the loop falls through silently and the
subsequent memory-region sanity check runs on the caller's
UNINITIALIZED stack value. When that garbage happens to carry the
expected region prefix bits, cl_dsp_get_reg() returns 0 and the
caller regmap-reads/writes a garbage register address on the chip.

On the Pixel Watch 2 this is not theoretical: AGM enumerates every
mixer control of the monaco snd card as soon as card_state goes
ONLINE, its read of 'A2H Level' (numid 150) reaches this path, and
the resulting garbage-address access hard-hangs the bus -- the SoC
dies in a silent PS_HOLD HARD_RESET with no kernel output, ~0.5s
after the ADSP comes up. Reproduced deterministically with an
amixer cget sweep: numids 1-149 survive, numid 150 resets the SoC.
Stock WearOS survives the same sweep only because its kernel build
leaves different stack garbage that fails the region check (-EFAULT).

Track whether the lookup matched and return -ENOENT if it did not,
so kcontrol accessors fail gracefully until the A2H/SVC coefficient
files are actually loaded.

Upstream-Status: Pending [genuine cirrus cl_dsp driver bug, present
                          upstream; should be submitted]

Signed-off-by: Florent Revest <revestflo@gmail.com>
---
 private/google-modules/amplifiers/cs40l26/cl_dsp.c | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

diff --git a/private/google-modules/amplifiers/cs40l26/cl_dsp.c b/private/google-modules/amplifiers/cs40l26/cl_dsp.c
--- a/private/google-modules/amplifiers/cs40l26/cl_dsp.c
+++ b/private/google-modules/amplifiers/cs40l26/cl_dsp.c
@@ -138,6 +138,7 @@
 	int ret = 0;
 	struct cl_dsp_coeff_desc *coeff_desc;
 	unsigned int mem_region_prefix;
+	bool found = false;
 
 	if (!dsp)
 		return -EPERM;
@@ -164,9 +165,17 @@
 			return -ENXIO;
 		}
 
+		found = true;
 		break;
 	}
 
+	if (!found) {
+		dev_dbg(dsp->dev,
+			"No DSP control called %s for algo 0x%X\n",
+			coeff_name, algo_id);
+		return -ENOENT;
+	}
+
 	/* verify register found in expected region */
 	switch (block_type) {
 	case CL_DSP_XM_PACKED_TYPE:
